article.headline: IPFW 58, South Dakota St 38
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- DeWitt Scott had 16 points and eight rebounds to lead Indiana-Purdue-Fort Wayne to a 58-38 victory over South Dakota State on Monday night. Justin Hawkins and D.J. Posley each scored 12 points for IPFW (7-15). Zeljko Egeric had nine rebounds for the Mastadons. Ben Beran had 14 points for South Dakota State (6-16), while Matt Caldwell added 12 points and eight rebounds. IPFW shot 42 percent from the field, while the Jackrabbits shot 36 percent, going 0-for-12 from 3-point range.
